Product Description

Named after the British expression describing a particularly rich and full wine, enjoy this Merlot aged in small oak barrels for four months producing a wine with deep purple hues and spicy, supple fruit. Made from the best vineyards in the hills north of Nimes in the Languedoc Roussillon region of Southern France.





Other Details


Country:

		France
	

Alc By Vol:

		12.5%
	

Vintage:

		2010
	





